headline: Raymond James Sees an Attractive Setup in These 2 ‘Strong Buy’ Stocks
summary: As December draws to a close and Christmas arrives, investors are pausing to look back and assess a year that never followed a simple script. Policy uncertainty lingered, and trade headlines remained unpredictable as President Trump continued to keep markets guessing. And yet, corporate earnings held up and equities proved surprisingly resilient. That staying power is exactly what stood out to Raymond James Chief Investment Officer Larry Adam, who sees 2025 as a reminder of how adaptable markets
